<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="See_also">See also</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=OpenGL&amp;action=edit&amp;section=26" title="Edit section: See also">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ARB_assembly_language" title="ARB assembly language">ARB assembly language</a> – OpenGL's legacy low-level shading language.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Comparison_of_OpenGL_and_Direct3D" title="Comparison of OpenGL and Direct3D">Comparison of OpenGL and Direct3D</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Glide_API" title="Glide API">Glide API</a> – A graphics API once used on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/3dfx_Interactive" title="3dfx Interactive">3dfx</a> Voodoo cards.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_OpenGL_programs" title="List of OpenGL programs">List of OpenGL programs</a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenAL" title="OpenAL">OpenAL</a> – Cross-platform audio library, designed to resemble OpenGL.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenGL_ES" title="OpenGL ES">OpenGL ES</a> – OpenGL for <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embedded_Systems" title="Embedded Systems" class="mw-redirect">Embedded Systems</a></li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=OpenGL_Mathematics&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="OpenGL Mathematics (page does not exist)">GLM</a> – C++ mathematics toolkit for OpenGL, based on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/GLSL" title="GLSL" class="mw-redirect">GLSL</a> syntax.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenSL_ES" title="OpenSL ES">OpenSL ES</a> – API for audio on embedded systems, developed by the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khronos_Group" title="Khronos Group">Khronos Group</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OpenVG" title="OpenVG">OpenVG</a> – API for accelerated 2D graphics, developed by the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Khronos_Group" title="Khronos Group">Khronos Group</a>.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RenderMan_Interface_Specification" title="RenderMan Interface Specification">RenderMan Interface Specification</a> (RISpec) – <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pixar" title="Pixar">Pixar</a>'s open API for photorealistic off-line rendering.</li>
<li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/VOGL" title="VOGL">VOGL</a> – a debugger for OpenGL</li>
</ul>
